s cycles, I can see the pattern is consistent with normal cron behavior—the \\\"running\\\" status just indicates an active cycle, while completed cycles show as \\\"done\\\" and failed ones show their error state. Since the DTLX monitor was already running at 21:37 UTC, this latest cycle at 22:50 UTC represents another routine check with no anomalies to report.\\n\\nNow I'm checking the active cron sessions to confirm stability: all three monitors (QLHV, Agent Status, and DTLX) are running normally, and there are no new failures or blockers in the system. Everything checks out, so I'm staying silent per the protocol.\"\n            },\n            {\n              \"type\": \"text\",\n              \"text\": \"No meaningful state changes detected. All critical sessions stable — cron cycling is normal behavior.\\n\\n**Silent.**\"\n            }\n          ],\n          \"api\": \"anthropic-messages\",\n          \"provider\": \"ahvholding\",\n          \"model\": \"AHV-Holding-DEV\",\n          \"usage\": {\n            \"input\": 29355,\n            \"output\": 605,\n            \"totalTokens\": 44310,\n            \"cacheRead\": 13944,\n            \"cacheWrite\": 406,\n            \"cost\": {\n              \"total\": 0\n            }\n          },\n          \"stopReason\": \"stop\",\n          \"timestamp\": 1776207089317,\n          \"responseId\": \"062df7f2ccd19cd84c91b91eac4484b0\",\n          \"__openclaw\": {\n            \"id\": \"41953702\",\n            \"seq\": 5\n          }\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"key\": \"agent:master-orchestrator:cron:e7885813-0446-4101-a171-941c2416848e\",\n      \"kind\": \"other\",\n      \"channel\": \"webchat\",\n      \"label\": \"Cron: Agent Status to Lead\",\n      \"displayName\": \"webchat:g-agent-master-orchestrator-cron-e7885813-0446-4101-a171-941c2416848e\",\n      \"deliveryContext\": {\n        \"channel\": \"webchat\"\n      },\n      \"updatedAt\": 1776206821307,\n      \"sessionId\": \"7c8a812